B.UT=new A.cm("kb_001",B.df,"How do I perform wudu (ritual ablution)?","\u0643\u064a\u0641 \u0623\u062a\u0648\u0636\u0623\u061f","Make the intention silently, say Bismillah, then: (1) wash both hands to the wrists three times; (2) rinse the mouth three times; (3) inhale and expel water from the nose three times; (4) wash the face from forehead-hairline to chin and ear-to-ear three times; (5) wash the right arm to the elbow three times, then the left; (6) wipe the head with wet hands once (and the ears, inner and outer); (7) wash the right foot to the ankle three times, then the left.",'Quran 5:6 ("O you who believe! When you rise to pray, wash\u2026"); method described in Sahih al-Bukhari 159 and Sahih Muslim 226.',"Order and number of repetitions are similar across madhahib; small differences exist, e.g. wiping the entire head vs. part of it.")
B.Uz=new A.cm("kb_002",B.df,"What are the five daily prayers and when are they performed?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0645\u0633 \u0648\u0623\u0648\u0642\u0627\u062a\u0647\u0627\u061f","Fajr \u2014 from true dawn until sunrise. Dhuhr \u2014 from when the sun has passed its zenith until an object's shadow equals its own length. Asr \u2014 from then until sunset. Maghrib \u2014 from sunset until the red twilight disappears. Isha \u2014 from the disappearance of twilight until midnight (or until true dawn). Each must be prayed within its time window.",'Quran 4:103 ("Prayer is enjoined on the believers at fixed times"); time windows from the Hadith of Jibril, Sunan Abi Dawud 393.',null)
B.UB=new A.cm("kb_003",B.df,"How many rakats are in each daily prayer?","\u0643\u0645 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0631\u0643\u0639\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0645\u0633\u061f","Fard (obligatory) rakats: Fajr 2, Dhuhr 4, Asr 4, Maghrib 3, Isha 4. The Prophet (peace be upon him) also prayed sunnah rakats around them; the most emphasised confirmed sunnahs are: 2 before Fajr, 4+2 around Dhuhr, 2 after Maghrib, 2 after Isha, plus the Witr at night.","Sahih al-Bukhari 1182 and Sahih Muslim 728 on confirmed sunnahs.",null)
B.Uu=new A.cm("kb_004",B.df,"What invalidates wudu?","\u0645\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0642\u0636 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0636\u0648\u0621\u061f","Anything that exits from the front or back passage (urine, stool, gas), deep sleep where awareness is lost, loss of consciousness (faint, drunkenness), and direct touching of private parts with the bare hand (per several madhahib).","Quran 5:6; Sahih al-Bukhari 137 (sleep + breaking of wind).","Whether touching a non-mahram of the opposite sex breaks wudu is a known difference among the madhahib \u2014 this is one place to follow your local scholar.")
B.UK=new A.cm("kb_005",B.df,"What are the conditions for the prayer to be valid?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u0634\u0631\u0648\u0637 \u0635\u062d\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0627\u0629\u061f","Be a Muslim, of sound mind, and (for prayers other than the mu'allaq cases) past the age of discernment. Have wudu (or tayammum if water is unavailable). Cover the awrah, face the Qibla, pray in a clean place wearing clean clothes, within the time window, with the niyyah (intention) for that specific prayer.","Quran 2:144 (Qibla); 4:43 and 5:6 (purity); 4:103 (time).",null)
B.UQ=new A.cm("kb_006",B.df,"What do I do if I miss a prayer?","\u0645\u0627\u0630\u0627 \u0623\u0641\u0639\u0644 \u0625\u0630\u0627 \u0641\u0627\u062a\u062a\u0646\u064a \u0635\u0644\u0627\u0629\u061f",'Pray it as soon as you remember, in its normal form. If you wake up after sunrise and missed Fajr, pray it then. The Prophet (peace be upon him) said: "Whoever forgets a prayer or sleeps through it, its expiation is to pray it when he remembers it."',"Sahih al-Bukhari 597; Sahih Muslim 684.",null)
B.Ux=new A.cm("kb_007",B.df,"How do I pray when travelling?","\u0643\u064a\u0641 \u0623\u0635\u0644\u064a \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0641\u0631\u061f","A traveller may shorten the four-rakat prayers (Dhuhr, Asr, Isha) to two rakats. Fajr and Maghrib remain unchanged. Combining Dhuhr with Asr, and Maghrib with Isha, in either of their times is also permitted on a journey.","Quran 4:101; Sahih Muslim 689 (shortening).",'Distance and duration thresholds for "travel" status differ among the madhahib; ~80 km is a common reference.')
B.UH=new A.cm("kb_008",B.df,"May I pray anywhere as long as the place is clean?","\u0647\u0644 \u064a\u062c\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0627\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0623\u064a \u0645\u0643\u0627\u0646 \u0637\u0627\u0647\u0631\u061f",'Yes. The Prophet (peace be upon him) said: "The earth has been made for me a place of prostration and a means of purification." Avoid places of impurity, graveyards, bathrooms, and other specifically forbidden spots. A small clean mat or piece of clean cloth on the ground is sufficient.',"Sahih al-Bukhari 438; Sahih Muslim 521.",null)
B.UF=new A.cm("kb_009",B.fc,"When and how do I make the intention for fasting Ramadan?","\u0645\u062a\u0649 \u0648\u0643\u064a\u0641 \u0623\u0646\u0648\u064a \u0635\u064a\u0627\u0645 \u0631\u0645\u0636\u0627\u0646\u061f","Make the intention each night before Fajr to fast the next day for Allah. The intention is in the heart and need not be spoken aloud. A general intention at the start of Ramadan is widely held to be sufficient by some scholars, but renewing nightly is safer.",'Sunan Abi Dawud 2454: "Whoever does not have the intention of fasting before Fajr, his fast is not valid."',null)
B.UA=new A.cm("kb_010",B.fc,"What invalidates the fast?","\u0645\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u064a \u064a\u0628\u0637\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0648\u0645\u061f","Eating or drinking intentionally, intentional vomiting, sexual intercourse during the day, the onset of menstrual or post-natal bleeding, and apostasy. If a person eats or drinks by genuine forgetfulness, the fast is not broken \u2014 they continue and Allah has fed them.","Sahih al-Bukhari 1933 and Sahih Muslim 1155 (forgetful eating); Quran 2:187.",null)
B.UM=new A.cm("kb_011",B.fc,"Who is exempt from fasting in Ramadan?","\u0645\u0646 \u064a\u0639\u0641\u0649 \u0645\u0646 \u0635\u064a\u0627\u0645 \u0631\u0645\u0636\u0627\u0646\u061f","The sick whose illness fasting would harm, travellers, menstruating and post-natal women, the elderly who cannot fast, and pregnant or breastfeeding women if fasting harms them or the child. Most cases require making up the missed days later; the permanently incapable feed a poor person for each missed day (fidya).","Quran 2:184-185.",null)
B.Uy=new A.cm("kb_012",B.fc,"What are suhoor and iftar?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u062d\u0648\u0631 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0625\u0641\u0637\u0627\u0631\u061f",'Suhoor is the pre-dawn meal eaten before Fajr; the Prophet (peace be upon him) said: "Take suhoor \u2014 there is blessing in it." Iftar is breaking the fast at sunset (Maghrib). The sunnah is to break the fast promptly with fresh or dried dates and water, then pray Maghrib.',"Sahih al-Bukhari 1923 (blessing in suhoor); Sahih al-Bukhari 1957 (prompt iftar with dates).",null)
B.UL=new A.cm("kb_013",B.fc,"What is fasting on the 10th of Muharram (the Day of Ashura)?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u0648 \u0635\u064a\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u0648\u0645 \u0639\u0627\u0634\u0648\u0631\u0627\u0621\u061f","A highly recommended sunnah fast that expiates the sins of the previous year. The Prophet (peace be upon him) encouraged also fasting the 9th alongside the 10th to differ from the People of the Book.","Sahih Muslim 1162; 1134.",null)
B.Ut=new A.cm("kb_014",B.jK,"What is zakat and on whom is it obligatory?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0643\u0627\u0629 \u0648\u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0646 \u062a\u062c\u0628\u061f","Zakat is the obligatory annual purification of wealth: every Muslim of full ownership over wealth that has reached the nisab and remained held for one lunar year pays a fixed share to specific categories of recipients. The most common form is 2.5% of cash and gold/silver after one Hijri year of holding.","Quran 9:60 (recipients); 2:43; many hadiths including Sahih al-Bukhari 1395.",null)
B.UN=new A.cm("kb_015",B.jK,"What is the nisab (minimum threshold) for zakat?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u0648 \u0646\u0635\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0643\u0627\u0629\u061f","For gold, 85 grams. For silver, 595 grams. For cash, the equivalent value of either threshold (most contemporary scholars use the silver nisab to be more generous to the poor; many use gold). Below the nisab, no zakat is due.","Hadiths in Sahih al-Bukhari 1447 and Sunan al-Tirmidhi 620.","Whether to use the gold or silver nisab for cash differs between scholars; both are valid choices.")
B.UP=new A.cm("kb_016",B.jK,"Who can receive zakat?","\u0645\u0646 \u064a\u0633\u062a\u062d\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0643\u0627\u0629\u061f","Eight categories named in the Quran: (1) the poor, (2) the needy, (3) those employed to administer the funds, (4) those whose hearts are to be reconciled, (5) freeing captives, (6) those in debt, (7) in the cause of Allah, (8) the wayfarer.","Quran 9:60.",null)
B.UI=new A.cm("kb_017",B.jL,"What conditions make Hajj obligatory upon a person?","\u0645\u0627 \u0634\u0631\u0648\u0637 \u0648\u062c\u0648\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062c\u061f",'Being Muslim, of sound mind, having reached puberty, being free, and having the physical and financial ability ("istita\'ah") to undertake the journey, including travel costs and provision for dependants left behind. For a woman, a mahram is also traditionally required for travel.','Quran 3:97: "Hajj is a duty owed to Allah by those who can find a way to it."',null)
B.UO=new A.cm("kb_018",B.jL,"What are the major pillars of Hajj?","\u0645\u0627 \u0623\u0631\u0643\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062c\u061f","The pillars (without which Hajj is invalid) are: (1) Ihram \u2014 entering the sacred state with the intention; (2) Wuquf at Arafah on 9 Dhu al-Hijjah; (3) Tawaf al-Ifada around the Kaaba; (4) Sa'i between Safa and Marwah. Other rites (stoning the jamarat, sacrifice, shaving) are obligatory but missing them requires expiation rather than invalidating the Hajj.","Sahih Muslim 1218 (the description of the Prophet's Hajj).",null)
B.Uq=new A.cm("kb_019",B.jL,"What is the difference between Hajj and Umrah?","\u0645\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0642 \u0628\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062c \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0645\u0631\u0629\u061f",'Hajj is the major pilgrimage performed in the first two weeks of Dhu al-Hijjah and is obligatory once in a lifetime for those able. Umrah ("the lesser pilgrimage") may be performed at any time of year and consists of Ihram, Tawaf, and Sa\'i, finishing with shaving or shortening the hair. Umrah is sunnah and highly recommended.',"Sahih al-Bukhari 1773 (\"'Umrah to 'Umrah is an expiation for what is between them, and the Hajj that is mabrur has no reward less than Paradise.\").",null)
B.UD=new A.cm("kb_020",B.jM,"How are Islamic prayer times calculated?","\u0643\u064a\u0641 \u062a\u062d\u0633\u0628 \u0645\u0648\u0627\u0642\u064a\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0627\u0629\u061f","They are derived from the position of the sun: Fajr begins at true dawn (a defined angle below the horizon, typically 18\xb0), Dhuhr at solar noon (after the sun passes its zenith), Asr when an object's shadow equals its own length (or twice for the Hanafi school), Maghrib at sunset, and Isha when twilight disappears (a defined angle, commonly 17\xb0-18\xb0).","Hadith of Jibril, Sunan Abi Dawud 393; modern angle-based methods follow the same descriptions.",null)
B.Uv=new A.cm("kb_021",B.jM,"When does Ramadan begin?","\u0645\u062a\u0649 \u064a\u0628\u062f\u0623 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0631\u0645\u0636\u0627\u0646\u061f","On the sighting of the new crescent moon (hilal) at the end of Sha'ban. If the moon is not seen on the 29th of Sha'ban, the month is completed as 30 days and Ramadan begins the next day. Many countries today use astronomical calculation to confirm sighting, but local moon-sighting committees remain authoritative.",'Sahih al-Bukhari 1909: "Fast when you see it [the crescent], and break the fast when you see it; if it is hidden from you, then complete the count of Sha\'ban as thirty days."',null)
B.Ur=new A.cm("kb_022",B.jM,"What is the Hijri calendar?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0642\u0648\u064a\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u062c\u0631\u064a\u061f","A lunar calendar of 12 months totalling about 354 days. It begins from the year of the Prophet's emigration (Hijra) from Mecca to Medina (corresponding to 622 CE). Months begin with the sighting of the new crescent moon, so dates rotate ~11 days earlier each Gregorian year.",'Quran 9:36 ("The number of months with Allah is twelve\u2026"); historical context in Sahih al-Bukhari 3934.',null)
B.UJ=new A.cm("kb_023",B.hK,"What are morning and evening adhkar?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u0623\u0630\u0643\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0628\u0627\u062d \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0627\u0621\u061f","A set of authenticated supplications and rememberance recited after Fajr (morning) and after Asr/before Maghrib (evening). They include verses such as Ayat al-Kursi, the last three suras of the Quran (al-Ikhlas, al-Falaq, al-Nas \u2014 three times), and short formulas asking Allah for protection and well-being. The Adhkar feature in this app contains many of them.","Compiled in works such as Hisn al-Muslim; individual du'as are in Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim, and Sunan al-Tirmidhi.",null)
B.UC=new A.cm("kb_024",B.hK,"How much Quran should I read daily?","\u0643\u0645 \u0623\u0642\u0631\u0623 \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0622\u0646 \u064a\u0648\u0645\u064a\u064b\u0627\u061f","There is no fixed obligation, but consistency is highly praised. Many companions and scholars recommended reciting at least one juz daily so the entire Quran is completed each month, with reflection rather than haste. Even a few verses with understanding is better than rushing many.",'Sahih Muslim 1849 ("The most beloved deeds to Allah are the most consistent, even if few"); Sahih al-Bukhari 5054 on Quran recitation in cycles of seven and thirty days.',null)
B.UR=new A.cm("kb_025",B.hK,"What is the importance of du\u02bf\u0101\u02be (supplication)?","\u0645\u0627 \u0623\u0647\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0639\u0627\u0621\u061f",'Du\u02bf\u0101\u02be is the worshipper\'s direct conversation with Allah and is itself a form of worship. The Prophet (peace be upon him) said: "Du\u02bf\u0101\u02be is worship." Best times include the last third of the night, while prostrating, between adhan and iqamah, and the last hour of Friday.',"Sunan al-Tirmidhi 2969; Sahih Muslim 482.",null)
B.UG=new A.cm("kb_026",B.hK,"What is the difference between sunnah and nafl prayers?","\u0645\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0642 \u0628\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0646\u0629 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0627\u0641\u0644\u0629\u061f",'All prayers other than the five obligatory ones are voluntary. Within these, "sunnah mu\'akkadah" are the strongly emphasised sunnahs the Prophet (peace be upon him) practised regularly (e.g. 2 before Fajr, 2 after Maghrib). "Nafl" is general voluntary prayer beyond those, such as Duha, Tahajjud, and Tarawih during Ramadan.',"Sahih Muslim 728; Sahih al-Bukhari 1182 on confirmed sunnahs.",null)
B.Us=new A.cm("kb_027",B.hL,"What basic foods are halal and which are clearly haram?","\u0645\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0637\u0639\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0631\u0645\u0629 \u0628\u0634\u0643\u0644 \u0623\u0633\u0627\u0633\u064a\u061f","Halal: most foods are permitted by default. Meat from livestock slaughtered with the name of Allah is halal; seafood is halal; all clean plant-based foods are halal. Clearly haram: pork and its derivatives, blood, the meat of an animal that died of itself, animals slaughtered to other than Allah, intoxicants (alcohol and similar substances).","Quran 2:173; 5:3; 5:90.",null)
B.Uw=new A.cm("kb_028",B.hL,"What is the basic Islamic guidance on modest dress?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0636\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0637 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0633\u0627\u0633\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u0628\u0627\u0633 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u061f","Both men and women cover their awrah and dress modestly. For men, the awrah is at minimum the area between the navel and the knee. For women in front of non-mahrams, the awrah is the entire body except commonly the face and hands; the head and chest are covered. Clothing should be loose, opaque, not imitating the opposite sex, and not extravagant.","Quran 24:30-31; 33:59; Sahih al-Bukhari 5546 on awrah.",'Specifics about face covering and what counts as "loose" differ among madhahib and cultural practice.')
B.UE=new A.cm("kb_029",B.hL,"What is the proper way to greet a Muslim?","\u0645\u0627 \u0647\u064a \u062a\u062d\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u062d\u064a\u062d\u0629\u061f",'"As-salamu alaykum" (Peace be upon you). The fuller form is "As-salamu alaykum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuh" (Peace, mercy, and blessings of Allah be upon you). The reply is to use the same or a better form: "Wa alaykum as-salam wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuh."','Quran 4:86 ("When you are greeted with a greeting, return one better than it or at least equivalent."); Sahih al-Bukhari 6234.',null)
B.US=new A.cm("kb_030",B.hL,"May a Muslim pray while wearing shoes?","\u0647\u0644 \u064a\u062c\u0648\u0632 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0644\u0627\u0629 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0639\u0627\u0644\u061f","Yes, if the shoes are clean of impurity. The Prophet (peace be upon him) sometimes prayed in his sandals. In modern carpeted mosques the practice is to remove shoes to keep the prayer area clean for everyone, which is also good etiquette. At home or outdoors on clean ground, wearing clean shoes is permitted.","Sahih al-Bukhari 386 and Sunan Abi Dawud 650 on praying in sandals; checking for impurity comes from Sunan Abi Dawud 650 as well.",null)
